<section class="bg-white relative">
    <div class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 md:p-16 lg:p-20 max-w-7xl mx-auto relative flex flex-col">
        <div class="flex flex-1 flex-col col-span-12">
                <h2 class="text-4xl tracking-tight leading-tight font-semibold text-gray-900">
                    Gramophone presents...... Mahler
                </h2>
            <div class="h-1 w-16 bg-red-700 my-6"></div>
                <p class="leading-8 text-base text-gray-900 text-lg">
                    Aug 03, 2022
                </p>
                            <p class="leading-8 text-base text-gray-900 text-lg font-medium">
                    Gramophone launched its latest 100-page special edition - on the works of Romantic composer Mahler - on 27 July, making it the latest in a series of spin offs for Mark Allen Group’s music division.
                </p>
        </div>
            <div class="flex flex-1 flex-col col-span-12">
                <div class="w-full overflow-hidden">
                    <img src="/media/51gmycfm/gramophone-mahler.png?anchor=center&amp;mode=crop&amp;quality=60&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;rnd=133040011125870000"
                         data-srcset="/media/51gmycfm/gramophone-mahler.png?anchor=center&amp;mode=crop&amp;quality=60&amp;width=160&amp;height=90&amp;rnd=133040011125870000 160w,/media/51gmycfm/gramophone-mahler.png?anchor=center&amp;mode=crop&amp;quality=60&amp;width=320&amp;height=180&amp;rnd=133040011125870000 320w,/media/51gmycfm/gramophone-mahler.png?anchor=center&amp;mode=crop&amp;quality=60&amp;width=480&amp;height=270&amp;rnd=133040011125870000 480w,/media/51gmycfm/gramophone-mahler.png?anchor=center&amp;mode=crop&amp;quality=60&amp;width=640&amp;height=360&amp;rnd=133040011125870000 640w,/media/51gmycfm/gramophone-mahler.png?anchor=center&amp;mode=crop&amp;quality=60&amp;width=800&amp;height=450&amp;rnd=133040011125870000 800w"
                         data-src="/media/51gmycfm/gramophone-mahler.png?anchor=center&amp;mode=crop&amp;quality=60&amp;width=1280&amp;height=720&amp;rnd=133040011125870000"
                         data-sizes="auto"
                         sizes="auto"
                         class="lazyload pt-8 sm:pt-12 md:pt-16 pb-2 sm:pb-6 md:pb-10" />
                </div>
            </div>

        <div class="page-description leading-8 text-base text-gray-900 text-lg mt-6">
            <p><em>Gramophone presents… Mahler</em>, representing nearly a century of criticism of the composer and performances of his work, was produced in large part from Gramophone’s extensive archive.</p>
<p>Martin Cullingford, Gramophone’s editor, explained that the magazine saw such success with its first special edition - a 100-page square-back book celebrating 250 years since Beethoven’s birth - that it felt only right to follow it up with volumes for Bach, Mozart, and now: Mahler.</p>
<p>Cullingford said: “It was designed to be a fascinating and beautifully-presented souvenir for the serious collector and new listener alike - and a wonderful showcase of what Gramophone is, and does.”</p>
<p>He added that each issue has been immensely enjoyable to research and prepare.</p>
<p>“Exploring the archives to produce them involves spending hours being reacquainted with the most thought-provoking insights from artists both current and no longer with us, and discovering the wisdom offered by our writers of the past.”</p>
<p>Gramophone’s next special edition, on film scores, will be published in the autumn of 2022.</p>
<p>The series’ success has spurred other magazines in the group to produce their own souvenir editions in the same format: Jazzwise has seen huge success, for example, with its <em>100 Jazz Albums that Shook the World</em>, and Songlines and Opera Now respectively with <em>The Music of West Africa</em> and <em>Great Tenors. </em></p>
<p>International Piano and Choir and Organ have likewise published well-received special editions.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

    
